- source metadata: agent, provider, model, tool version\n+- latest user/assistant previews, with provider-internal events avoided or\n+  clearly labeled where possible\n+- observed branch/review/change targets seen in the related turns\n+\n+Do not hydrate or return full transcript records from `sessions`.\n+\n+### Slice 2: Compact `timeline`\n+\n+Goal: answer \"what happened in this session, and which turns should I read?\"\n+\n+Command:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog timeline <session-key> [--limit N]\n+```\n+\n+Return one compact entry per shown turn:\n+\n+- turn index\n+- `turn_key`\n+- `previous_turn_key`\n+- `capture_kind`\n+- `captured_at`\n+- `record_count`\n+- turn-local record range\n+- source `record_index` range, clearly labeled as provider/source indexes\n+- first/latest record timestamps\n+- environment snapshot status\n+- observed branch/review/change targets\n+- latest useful user/assistant previews\n+- compact record kind counts and top tool names\n+\n+Include coverage metadata:\n+\n+- `shown_turns`\n+- `total_turns`\n+- `has_more_before`\n+- `has_more_after`\n+\n+It is okay for the implementation to scan existing transcript records\n+internally. The important part is that the command output stays compact.\n+\n+### Slice 3: Bounded `records`\n+\n+Goal: answer \"show me the actual transcript records for this turn.\"\n+\n+Command:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> [--from start|end|<offset>] [--limit N]\n+```\n+\n+Behavior:\n+\n+- default `--from end`\n+- default to a conservative limit\n+- return records in natural transcript order within the selected window\n+- page by turn-local ordinal position in `TurnDetail.records`\n+- include provider/source `record_index` as record metadata, not as the cursor\n+- include `has_more_before`, `has_more_after`, `previous_from`, and `next_from`\n+\n+Do not add kind/path/error filtering in v1.\n+\n+### Slice 4: Workflow Note Or Skill\n+\n+Goal: teach agents how to use the primitives.\n+\n+Document the intended catch-up flow:\n+\n+1. run `sessions branch`\n+2. inspect recent multi-turn sessions first\n+3. use `timeline` to pick relevant turns\n+4. read `records` from the end of those turns\n+5. page backward only when the current state or user intent is unclear\n+\n+This should remain a workflow layered on primitives, not a magic `handoff`\n+command.\n+\n+### Explicitly Out Of Scope For This Build\n+\n+- storage rewrite\n+- persisted generated summaries\n+- parent/child session inference\n+- automatic main-session selection\n+- search\n+- record filtering\n+- path indexes\n+- commit indexes\n+- product-specific review or handoff APIs\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:56:45.087Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}